  "image_url": "https://cdn.kirtansewa.net/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/22013028/Bhai-Dawinder-Singh-Shant-2.jpg",
  "body": [
    "Bhai Dawinder Singh Shant was born in the historical city of Assandh in Karnal disctrict, Haryana. Slightly off topic, Assandh is home to a 2000 year old Buddhist stupa which is said to be the largest in the country, towering at 25 meters in height and 75 meters in diameter. Just thought I’d highlight its existence as this historical site has been neglected and there isn’t much awareness created in regards to tourism. Back to the topic, Bhai Dawinder Singh started his training in vocals and tabla with Bhai Gurmeet Singh Shant who has passed on his vast knowledge of Gurmat Sangeet including puratan compositions, guldastas, taranas to Bhai Dawinder Singh. From 1987 to 1994, he remained on the side harmonium and provided backing vocals for Bhai Gurmeet Singh Shant’s jatha along with Bhai Manjeet Singh on tabla. During this time, their jatha visited Malaysia and Singapore and captivated the sangat. I shall be uploading those recordings on Bhai Gurmeet Singh Shant’s page in the near future. Please look out for that.  In 1994, he formed his own jatha and has toured around the world since. Currently, he resides in Delhi and performs regular Kirtan duties in the various historical Gurdwaras in Delhi. In addition to his training with Bhai Gurmeet Singh Shant, he has also learned from renowned music director, Ustad Jaswant Singh Bhanwra. If anyone would like to share more recordings of Bhai Dawinder Singh Shant, please contact us.",
    "The next batch of recordings are from the Gurmat Sangeet Project website. Please check out their website at the following link for more wonderful Kirtan http://www.gurmatsangeetproject.com/index.htm"
  ],
